claim.claim-text:
1. A structure comprising:
a first layer comprising a first semiconductor material disposed above a substrate, the first semiconductor material being strained;
a second layer disposed above the first layer, the second layer comprising a second semiconductor material different from the first semiconductor material;
a transistor gate electrode and a sidewall spacer disposed above the second layer, the transistor gate electrode and sidewall spacer defining a first region disposed thereunder, the first region comprising a first portion of each of the first layer and the second layer; and
a third material disposed laterally from the first region, the third material extending into the first layer and the second layer,
wherein at least one of a composition or defect density of the third material is different from a composition or defect density of the first region.

15. A semiconductor structure comprising:
a substrate having a first region and a second region;
a first semiconductor layer over the substrate in the first region and the second region;
a second semiconductor layer over the first semiconductor layer and in the first region and the second region;
a first transistor in the first region; and
a second transistor in the second region,
wherein at least a portion of the second semiconductor layer in the first region is strained, and at least a portion of the second semiconductor layer in the second region is relaxed.
